## Description {#details}

A class representing an address table as specified in DWARF v5.

The table consists of a header followed by an array of address values from .debug&#95;addr section.

Definition at line 26 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfdebugaddr-h">DWARFDebugAddr.h</a>.

### SegSize {#a93c9dc4f9add5c96414ada399baecbd4}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint8&#95;t llvm::DWARFDebugAddrTable::SegSize</>}>
The size in bytes of a segment selector on the target architecture.

If the target system uses a flat address space, this value is 0.
